Ekiti State Governor Kayode Fayemi on Sunday said he has recovered and tested negative for the coronavirus “Back to the grind. Second test negative. I’m now definitely free of COVID-19. Thanks to all for your support,” Fayemi tweeted. In July, Fayemi joined a growing list of state governors and other high profile Nigerians who tested positive for coronavirus.  Governors of Kaduna, Oyo, Bauchi, Ebonyi, Ondo and Delta states tested positive and have since recovered from the virus. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .